Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm becoming a coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can no longer be playing myself{guess: no clue what this "kaoyousumasu" part is - maybe "I have to find someone to represent" or "since its condition became public"} \Nwith this good-for-nothing body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.75,0:04:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I'll seek a player \Nworth putting my everything into.{Lit: I will look for a player who'll accept my everything. - no clue why he says "accept" whereas he clearly used stronger and more domineering constructions like "bet on" or "put into" or "devote my life to" so I'm not keeping it to avoid a chagrin of explaining + he clearly compelled Hiromi, with or without her consent}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.06,0:04:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere... \NSomewhere, there has to be one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.50,0:04:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo, when the time comes, can I expect you \Nto take over that player from where I leave off{/halfway through/en route}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.63,0:04:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by years of tempering, \Nyou can bring up a good player.{/Lit: Without devoting a long time to it, you cannot become a player.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.89,0:04:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Two or three years is nowhere near enough.\NThat's why I ask you to lend me some of your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When the time comes for me \Nto bid farewell to this earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.48,0:04:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd prefer to fuse into a guiding{added for contrast} light,{/ascend to the stars,} \Nthan to get lost in the darkness of times.{/to descend into eternal night.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time{guess: no idea for this "wassu"} to pass it over to Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.94,0:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask you to lend{it's exclusively the same verb as 4 lines before} me some {of your }strength, Munakata!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.69,0:05:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.11,0:05:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:29.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munakata Jin
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.48,0:05:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Munakata's racket!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.77,0:05:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You will turn up on the court once again, \Nholding this racket, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.77,0:06:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so cruel! \NDon't you have a heart!?{/You're so insensitive/brutal!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.90,0:06:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still trying to figure what to do next!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.98,0:06:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Death is not an option for me, \Nyet I can't go on living like this as well!{/but living this way is unbearable as well!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.99,0:06:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then... \NThen you tell me to pick up the racket again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.08,0:06:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, you want me \Nto rob Coach Munakata off his racket?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.00,0:06:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my 14th spring. \NI just enrolled in Nishi High.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when I saw a butterfly \Nfluttering about in the sakura petals{/flowers}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.09,0:06:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorgeous, elegant,{guess; "yuugan"} and beautiful. \NThat was Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.97,0:06:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I even joined the tennis club \Njust to play tennis alongside her{/such a person} every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.39,0:06:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, to just stand on the same court\N{without playing myself} would have been enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that... That was my initial motive \Nfor joining the tennis club.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.13,0:06:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, Coach Munakata's path crossed mine.{/appeared before/barged in/came across/approached}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.32,0:06:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I was selected against all odds, \Nso Coach had to be especially demanding.{/Because Coach selected me as an exception to an exception, he went particularly hard/strict/harsh on me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I considered quitting tennis countless times!{/How many times I thought of quitting tennis!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But on each such occasion{/time}, \Nthe look in Coach Munakata's eyes was telling me:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.70,0:07:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oka, keep following me. \NTrust me to show you the way to brilliance!"{/Give me more of your trust!"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.65,0:07:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how... That's how I managed \Nto keep going with tennis for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.21,0:07:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It was through tennis \Nthat I got to know so many great{added} people!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.01,0:07:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly, Midorikawa, \NTodo, Ozaki and Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.13,0:07:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I met everyone \Nthanks to Coach Munakata introducing me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.52,0:07:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way I could make it this far \Nis thanks to Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.52,0:07:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But Coach is no more! \NSo my tennis is no more as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You are waiting for me \Nto yell, "Stop, don't do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.88,0:08:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, deciding whether to die or to live \Nis a matter of one's personal volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't no one is in position \Nto meddle with this decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.79,0:10:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, it's training time, \Nlet's go running.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.42,0:10:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Eyes open,{/Open your eyes and wake up,} Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You were brought up by Munakata himself! \NThere's no way you give up{guess in the "nyou wo" part} so soon!{/You cannot be exhausted already!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.99,0:10:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Munakata is no more.\NPlease refrain from mentioning Coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the sea, Jin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.01,0:11:43.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nishi Medical University {Supplementary }Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:56.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\c&HB5B9DD&\3c&H1A2FED&}Operation underway
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.19,0:12:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go? \NYou informed Midorikawa's parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I contacted the place \Nthey're visiting next{/should soon arrive to; he just says "the destination" but I'm at a loss as to the destination of what and in what relation}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.55,0:12:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if they burn the rubber, \Nthey'll only return by tomorrow morning.{/however hurriedly, they can't get back until ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.58,0:12:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.16,0:12:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.08,0:12:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi? Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.80,0:12:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa's... \NHow is Midorikawa's condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.20,0:12:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you even seen yourself!?{/Instead, what about your condition?!} \NWhat in the world has happened? How did it come to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't wibble-wobble{ me off}!{/Lies, all lies!}{deliberate mistranslation as I fancy my variant more} \NYou look too macabre{/morbid/eerie} to shake me off!{/I can clearly see something's off with you!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.18,0:12:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You ain't no the usual Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so weird! \NSo macabre! Macabre...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.91,0:12:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.43,0:13:06.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\c&HB5B9DD&\3c&H1A2FED&}Operation underway
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.02,0:13:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.61,0:13:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.75,0:13:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For all's sake, what the hell happened to Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.02,0:13:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks so emaciated and worn out{/exhausted/wilted}.{guess: only half sure about "yatsurei" being "wilted" and still no clue about "tatabochiwanai"; alternatively it may lowkey be "his example" and accordingly: He really is subjecting her to all those practices/to everything he went through himself/making her follow his example/path.}\NJust what is Katsura trying to do to Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.20,0:13:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki, we entrusted Oka wholly to Katsura's custody.\NWe can no longer have a say in her recovery process{added in her recovery}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.23,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.22,0:13:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What else... What else you think is there \Nwe can do for her now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.20,0:13:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.76,0:14:05.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\c&HB5B9DD&\c&HB3B8DE&\3c&H1320ED&\t(700,1650,\c&H3B1005&\3c&H893312&)}Operation underway
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.66,0:14:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Finished!{/It's over!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.83,0:14:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We made every effort.{/did our best.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.02,0:14:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet we barely managed to put her leg back together \Nand{/in addition to the leg fracture,} the head hit the asphalt pretty hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.34,0:14:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight will be a crucial point{/This night will decide everything}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, we're rushing her \Nto intensive care unit for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.84,0:14:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.94,0:14:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Be careful! \N- I'll get the elevator.{guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.32,0:14:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.52,0:14:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong!{/Don't leave us!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.71,0:14:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! This can't be!{/is a no way!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.19,0:14:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot die!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.78,0:14:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Racket...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.33,0:14:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it? \NWhat was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.46,0:14:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Racket...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.93,0:14:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My racket...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.58,0:15:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's return,{/go home,} Oka. \NWe overstayed our welcome here.{/there's nothing else we need in this place.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.54,0:15:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Be not intimidated{/terrified/dreaded/affected/impressed}, Oka. \NYou cannot alter the life's ways, neither the death's ones.{I'm actually completely dumbfounded at what he meant to say here with "People dying is an actual reality/hard fact. And living is ... as well." Maybe it's a variation on "God works in mysterious ways" or "you cannot change it even if you're afraid" so I combined the two}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.14,0:15:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When facing a fate of death, \Nanyone{/anything} is powerless.{although he uses a completely different construction, I'm self-citing myself from ep7 here because I fancy such little refrains in subs; besides, it's a lot more faithful to original line here}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like one is powerless to attach any significance to the trifling process of hitting the tennis ball{ without any underlying idea}.{/Just like when you merely hit the ball in tennis, this action is utterly meaningless./Much like the simple game of tennis, where each hit on the ball is initially devoid of any significance./In a way, life is like a game of tennis that consists of meaningless strokes on the balls.}{XD}{yeah I went hard on this line if you can't tell, the point is, the series contradicts itself here: it previously advocated the idea that each stroke is unique}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.95,0:16:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet {/there's no telling if }this very trifling tennis may too reciprocate by \Nsomehow doing you a service when survival is questioned.{/by becoming the sole thing that keeps you alive one day./crucial for your survival at a moment when it's jeopardized./Yet even this trifling game may do you a great service when you least expect./Yet through this trivial game of tennis,one can apply the significance to/engender ... in his life.}{this line is nigh entirely made up, but I completely lost the track of katsura's thought as Lit would be "But this simple tennis can too be of some use/may help you in some way when living the life/for the survival process."}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.87,0:16:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.30,0:16:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,racket...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.84,0:16:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of service?{/How can it be of use?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.80,0:16:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably, insignificant{/trifling/no big deal} as well.{/of a trivial kind as well./not in the obvious way.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In the great variety of major indicators \Nthat can tell you for certain you're still alive,{he uses particularly intricate contraptions of words to express that like he always does}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.27,0:16:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll serve you{impersonal clause is totally normal in JP but it absolutely sucks in EN to have to jump from "you" to "one" between lines} no more \Nbut one miniscule oblique cue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.79,0:16:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But to one, even this minuscule oblique cue \Ncan be a motive driving his hand forward.{invented to make more consistent with Oka looking at her hand}{/can give a reason to live on.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.57,0:17:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Todo. \NGood morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.44,0:17:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She stabilized.{/is safe.} The worst is already over.{crisis is already averted.} \NHer attending physician said so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.66,0:17:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.04,0:17:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a minute please. \NOne more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... I guess there's nothing I can do on my side?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.78,0:17:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.67,0:17:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka... To help Oka, \Nif there's anything I can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.82,0:17:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...not. Not a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.20,0:17:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad. If you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However, to dispel your worries,\Nyou're free to come see her, whenever.{/anytime.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.81,0:17:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just keep in mind that you will thus trade {slight }anxiety \Nfor an unmitigated torment.{/Just don't forget that you will probably be the prime victim of the agonizing thoughts to follow.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.12,0:19:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop running away, Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.73,0:19:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be tormenting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.26,0:19:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be heartbreaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.85,0:19:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you shouldn't be running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.43,0:19:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Confront it head on, {do it }as someone \Nwho Munakata would choose against all odds!{added for spiciness}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.81,0:19:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, the same way you do now, I was myself \Nsuccumbing{/giving way} to unbearable pressure of Munakata's death.{/the burden of Munakata's death fate laid heavy on me just like it did on you now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.30,0:19:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the first time \NI got to see Munakata in that light.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.01,0:19:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Even for a tough nut like Munakata, \Ndeath turned out to be too irresistible and immense a force.{/Even a guy like Munakata didn't have a slightest sway over something as tremendous as death.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.44,0:19:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, Oka. \NFor you will only hear it once.{/Listen, Oka. Remember just this one thing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.19,0:19:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The comprehension{/realization/coming to know} of Munakata's death \Nsent me straight to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.03,0:20:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I agonized, I lurked in the shadows, \N{hiding from it }for the last 5 years.{/I wandered around in circles/crawled from place to place/groveled in shock/was trying to look the other way/tried to crawl away from it/did my best to forget it/went on detours to escape the fact}{it seems to be a pretty clear set phrase but I'm still clueless as to what "turning crawling" may represent here}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.57,0:20:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet my season{added for flavor} of wailing lasts{/I never managed to escape ...} to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.91,0:20:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't believe it will ever expire.{/last forever}{/I even accepted I will forever stay in it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, even now, the deep cut that Munakata's death \Nleft in my chest still pains me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.12,0:20:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as the blood of remorse keeps flowing.{Lit: Therefore, even now Munakata's death with a big scar in my chest makes the blood of regret keep flowing steadily./And thus, Munakata's death keeps resounding in my chest, contaminating the blood with chagring from that deep mark.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! Even now, like many years ago,{invented} \NI can't help bursting into tears, thinking of Munakata.{added many years ago because I'm not sure for "korentatte" meaning}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.15,0:20:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, don't try to forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it as a proof{/in sight}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.32,0:20:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it constantly within sight \Nas a reminder{guess: can't grasp that "taitsa" part} that you cannot revert Munakata's death!{it's "a hard fact/reality" again, so I'm kinda sticking with my previous wording}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.16,0:20:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then move on! \NGet up and start walking.{/Doesn't matter where./Wherever.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.27,0:20:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you are supplied with more courage, \Nmore chest-sundering sorrow{/anguish that feels like your chest is falling apart} than anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.48,0:20:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you must yourself choose living this way!{that's quite literal, but I still don't get the point}{/As someone endowed than more courage than that of an ordinary person, and with that heartbreaking pain in your chest, you should deliberately carry on this way of living!}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.85,0:21:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit it, Oka. Direct all your thoughts \Ntowards{/Put your mind entirely into} this yellow ball, then smash it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.51,0:21:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.07,0:21:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Smash it hard{added}, Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.19,0:21:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going in{/ go ahead/'m starting [to go]/Here I go/will serve now/'m moving on}, Coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.08,0:23:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A message from Aikawa Maki!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.08,0:23:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God, \NHiromi regained her tennis again, at last!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.72,0:23:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But who'd guess, \NKatsura went all-in on her{guess: tokku} at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.20,0:23:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a super-hard trial! \NWhile her body is still not quite in shape.{/she cannot move well enough yet.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.76,0:23:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's making me so extra worried with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.96,0:23:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Hiromi!
